    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Mojave Desert</b> (322Ad, Aj, Al). Stands of <i>Purshia stansburiana </i>occur in the Clark, Ivanpah, New York, Funeral and Providence mountains, while stands of <i>Mortonia utahensis</i> occur in the Funeral and Clark Mountains (Thomas et al. 2004, Evens et al. 2014).</li>
        
            <li><b>Southeastern Great Basin</b> (341Fc-d, Ff). Stands of <i>Purshia stansburiana </i>occur in the Cottonwood, Grapevine, and Panamint mountains, and are likely to occur in the Inyo, Last Chance, and White mountains.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> This alliance is rare and localized in California. Impacts are likely minimal, with the possible exception of mining and quarrying in some locations. </div>
</div>

    

    

